Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
bindKey(25.10)                                                  bindKey(25.10)

Name
       bindKey - Enables you to create keyboard shortcuts

Syntax
         bindKey <key><cmd>

       [-help]

       Enables you to create keyboard shortcuts.

       You  can  use this command at any time after starting the Innovus soft-
       ware.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each bindkey parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

               man bindkey

       <key>  Specifies the key to be used as the shortcut. You can specify a:

              * Single Key-Specify any one of the following keys:

                     * a - z

                     * Function keys: use F1 - F12

                     * Arrow keys: use Up Down Left Right

                     * Number keys

                     * Unshifted punctuation keys: .,/-=

                     * Other keys: use Space, Delete, Backspace, or Esc

              * Shift Key Combination-Specify Shift as the first key  followed
                by '-' followed by:

                     * A - Z

                     * One of the 'shifted' punctuation chars: ~@#$%^&*()_+

                     * Function keys: use F1 - F12

                     * Arrow keys: use Up Down Left Right

                     * Other keys: use Space, Delete, Backspace, or Esc

              * Ctrl/Alt  Key Combination-Specify Ctrl or Alt as the first key
                followed by '+' followed by any of the single keys above

              Data_type: string, optional

       <cmd>  Specifies the command to be executed when key is pressed.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * Runs the fit command when you press f on your keyboard:

                bindKey f "fit"

              * The following example shows how to use bindKey when  #  and  @
                keys are pressed from GUI.

                bindKey  Shift-@ "setPreference StretchRectilinear 1; setPref-
                erence StretchRestriction 1"

                bindKey Shift-# "setPreference StretchRectilinear 0;  setPref-
                erence StretchRestriction 0"

Related Information
              * Binding Key section of View Menu in Innovus Menu Reference

